# React Native Template — Mimax Code Rules

## Project Overview

- **Tech Stack**: React Native 0.84, TypeScript, Redux Toolkit + redux-saga, TanStack React Query v5, twrnc, react-hook-form + yup, React Navigation v7, i18next, MMKV, axios
- **Path Alias**: `~` maps to `src/`

## 1. General Conventions

### Naming Conventions

| Entity               | Convention                                     | Example                           |
| -------------------- | ---------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| Components / Screens | `PascalCase.tsx`                               | `Login.tsx`, `FormInput.tsx`      |
| Feature files        | `feature.type.ts`                              | `auth.slice.ts`, `auth.saga.ts`   |
| Interfaces / Types   | `PascalCase`                                   | `SignInPayload`, `AuthState`      |
| Enums                | `PascalCase` (no `Enum` suffix except storage) | `AppRoutes`, `StorageEnum`        |
| Hooks                | `use` prefix                                   | `useBaseQuery`, `useAppBootstrap` |
| Redux actions        | `featureNameActions`                           | `signInActions`                   |
| Selectors            | `select` prefix                                | `selectIsAuthenticated`           |
| Services             | `camelCase.service.ts`                         | `auth.service.ts`                 |

### File Naming

| Type             | Convention                              | Example                              |
| ---------------- | --------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| Components       | `PascalCase.tsx`                        | `UserProfile.tsx`, `FormInput.tsx`   |
| Hooks            | `camelCase.ts` with `use` prefix        | `useAuth.ts`, `useFormValidation.ts` |
| Services         | `camelCase.service.ts`                  | `auth.service.ts`, `api.service.ts`  |
| Utils/Helpers    | `camelCase.ts` or `camelCase.helper.ts` | `date.helper.ts`, `format.ts`        |
| Types/Interfaces | `PascalCase.type.ts` or co-located      | `auth.type.ts`, `user.type.ts`       |
| Constants        | `camelCase.ts` or `PascalCase.ts`       | `storage.ts`, `routes.ts`            |

### Variable Naming

| Type           | Convention                   | Example                                |
| -------------- | ---------------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| Variables      | `camelCase`                  | `userName`, `isLoading`, `hasError`    |
| Booleans       | `is`/`has`/`can` prefix      | `isValid`, `hasPermission`, `canEdit`  |
| Arrays         | plural noun or `List` suffix | `users`, `items`, `userList`           |
| Functions      | verb + noun (camelCase)      | `getUser`, `fetchData`, `onSubmit`     |
| Event handlers | `on` prefix                  | `onChange`, `onPress`, `onSubmit`      |
| Callbacks      | `handle` prefix              | `handleChange`, `handleSubmit`         |
| State          | descriptive noun             | `userData`, `formValues`, `selectedId` |

### Type & Interface Naming

```ts
// ✅ Interfaces — PascalCase with descriptive suffix
interface UserProfile { ... }
interface AuthState { ... }
interface FormInputProps { ... }

// ✅ Type aliases — PascalCase
type UserId = string;
type ApiResponse<T> = { data: T; error: string | null };
type OnClickCallback = () => void;

// ✅ Enums — PascalCase (no 'Enum' suffix except StorageEnum)
enum AppRoutes { HOME = 'Home', LOGIN = 'Login' }
enum StorageEnum { ACCESS_TOKEN, REFRESH_TOKEN }

// ✅ Props interfaces — PascalCase with 'Props' suffix
interface ButtonProps { label: string; onPress: () => void; }
interface ModalProps { visible: boolean; children: React.ReactNode; }
```

### File Structure Rules

- Every folder must have a barrel `index.ts` for clean imports
- Use `~` path alias instead of relative `../../` imports
- Folder structure:
  - `src/components/` — Reusable, presentational only (no Redux, no navigation)
  - `src/containers/` — Screen-level components (logic lives here)
  - `src/features/<name>/` — Redux feature modules
  - `src/hooks/` — Custom hooks
  - `src/services/` — API services
  - `src/types/` — Type definitions

## 2. Component Patterns

### Export Pattern

Every component file MUST have **both** named export AND default export:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
export function MyComponent(props: MyComponentProps) { ... }
export default MyComponent;

// ❌ BAD
export const MyComponent = (props: MyComponentProps) => { ... };
```

### Barrel index.ts Pattern

Split components and types into two clearly separated sections:

```ts
// ✅ index.ts
// ─── Components ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
export { default as MyComponent } from './MyComponent';

// ─── Props ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
export type { MyComponentProps } from './MyComponent';
```

Common mistakes to avoid:

```ts
// ❌ BAD — interleaved exports (mixing component with type)
export { default as MyComponent } from './MyComponent';
export type { MyComponentProps } from './MyComponent';
export { default as AnotherComponent } from './AnotherComponent';
export type { AnotherComponentProps } from './AnotherComponent';

// ❌ BAD — named-only export (barrel must use 'default as' pattern)
export { MyComponent } from './MyComponent';
```

### Props Typing

Define props as a local `interface` or `type` above the component:

```tsx
interface MyComponentProps {
  value: string;
  onChange: (value: string) => void;
}

export function MyComponent({ value, onChange }: MyComponentProps) { ... }
```

## 3. Styling (twrnc)

### Import

Always import the shared `tw` instance:

```ts
import tw from '~configs/tw';
```

### No Inline Styles

Never write inline style objects directly on JSX elements:

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<View style={{ flex: 1, backgroundColor: 'white', padding: 16 }} />

// ✅ GOOD
<View style={tw`flex-1 bg-white p-4`} />
```

### Use twrnc for Conditional Styles

```tsx
// ✅ Template literal for static classes
<View style={tw`flex-1 bg-white p-4`} />

// ✅ tw.style() for conditional/merged classes
<View style={tw.style('flex-1', isActive && 'bg-primary')} />

// ✅ Array to combine tw + StyleSheet
<View style={[tw`rounded-2xl`, styles.sheet]} />
```

### StyleSheet.create

Only for values NOT expressible as Tailwind classes (rgba, percentage heights):

```tsx
const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  overlay: { backgroundColor: 'rgba(0,0,0,0.5)' },
});
```

### Custom Colors

The only custom color is `primary: '#1E40AF'` — use `bg-primary`, `text-primary`, etc.

### Dark Mode

```tsx
<View style={tw`bg-white dark:bg-gray-900`} />
```

## 4. State Management

### Two-track Architecture

| Track                        | Tool                       | Use For                    |
| ---------------------------- | -------------------------- | -------------------------- |
| Global / persistent UI state | Redux Toolkit + redux-saga | Auth session, user profile |
| Server / async data          | TanStack React Query       | API calls, caching         |

### Redux Feature Structure

Each feature lives in `src/features/<name>/` with:

- `auth.actions.ts` — createRequestActions triplets
- `auth.saga.ts` — watchers + workers
- `auth.slice.ts` — state shape + extraReducers
- `auth.selector.ts` — memoized selectors
- `auth.helpers.ts` — pure helper functions (transform data, format values, validate)
- `index.ts` — barrel export

### auth.helpers.ts Pattern

Pure functions that transform data or handle business logic without side effects:

```ts
// ✅ auth.helpers.ts
export const formatUserName = (firstName: string, lastName: string): string => {
  return `${lastName} ${firstName}`.trim();
};

export const validateToken = (token: string | null): boolean => {
  if (!token) return false;
  try {
    // validate token logic
    return true;
  } catch {
    return false;
  }
};
```

**When to use helpers:**

- Data transformation (format date, currency, name)
- Validation logic (not for forms — that's yup)
- Business rules calculations
- Pure computations without side effects

### Redux Actions

Use `createRequestActions` helper (DO NOT manually create action creators):

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
export const signInActions = createRequestActions<
  SignInPayload,
  SignInResponse
>('auth/signIn');

// ❌ BAD
const signInRequest = createAction<SignInPayload>('auth/signInRequest');
```

### Redux Selectors

Always memoize with `createSelector`:

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
export const selectIsAuthenticated = createSelector(
  selectAuthToken,
  token => !!token,
);

// ❌ BAD — inline derivation without memoization
const isAuth = useAppSelector(state => !!state.auth.token);
```

## 5. React Query Hooks

**Always prefer the 3 base hooks** over calling `useQuery` / `useMutation` / `useInfiniteQuery` directly.

### API Hooks Pattern

For feature-specific API calls, create custom hooks in `src/hooks/api/` folder:

```
src/hooks/api/
├── auth.ts     # useLogin, useSignUp, useProfile, etc.
├── post.ts     # usePosts, useCreatePost, etc.
└── index.ts    # barrel export
```

```ts
// ✅ src/hooks/api/auth.ts
import { useBaseQuery, useBaseMutation } from '~hooks';

export const useLogin = () => {
  return useBaseMutation<AuthResponse, LoginPayload>({
    url: '/auth/login',
    method: 'POST',
  });
};

export const useProfile = (userId: string) => {
  return useBaseQuery<UserProfile>({
    url: `/users/${userId}`,
    queryKey: ['profile', userId],
  });
};

// ✅ Components use the API hook directly
const LoginScreen = () => {
  const { mutate, isPending } = useLogin();
  // ...
};
```

```ts
// ✅ src/hooks/api/index.ts
export * from './auth';
export * from './post';
```

**Benefits:**

- Components don't need to know the API URL/method
- Easy to add caching, polling, or transformations in one place
- Centralized API configuration per feature
- Easier to mock in tests

### useBaseQuery — for GET requests

```tsx
const { data, isLoading, isError } = useBaseQuery<UserProfile>({
  url: '/profile',
  queryKey: ['profile', userId],
});
```

### useBaseMutation — for POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE

```tsx
const { mutate, isPending } = useBaseMutation<SignInResponse, SignInPayload>({
  url: '/auth/sign-in',
  method: 'POST',
  options: {
    onSuccess: data => {
      /* handle success */
    },
  },
});

mutate({ data: { email, password } });
```

### useBaseInfinite — for paginated lists

```tsx
const { data, fetchMore, hasNextPage, total, isLoading } = useBaseInfinite<
  ListResponse,
  unknown,
  { page: number; limit: number }
>({
  url: '/posts',
  params: { limit: 20 },
  pageParamKey: 'page',
  totalKey: 'total',
  keyArray: 'data',
});
```

### Error Handling

Handle errors at the **component level** — the hook handles the request, you handle the UI:

```tsx
const { data, isLoading, isError, error } = useBaseQuery<UserProfile>({
  url: '/profile',
});

// ✅ Handle error at component level
if (isError) {
  return <ErrorMessage message={error?.message || 'Something went wrong'} />;
}

// ❌ BAD — try-catch inside component logic (use options.onError in mutation)
try {
  const result = await fetchData();
} catch (e) {
  // handle error
}
```

For mutations, use `options.onError` callback:

```tsx
const { mutate } = useBaseMutation<UserResponse, UserPayload>({
  url: '/users',
  method: 'POST',
  options: {
    onError: error => {
      // Show toast, log to analytics, etc.
      console.error('Create user failed:', error);
    },
  },
});
```

### Decision Guide

| Scenario                                      | Hook to use       |
| --------------------------------------------- | ----------------- |
| Read data (GET)                               | `useBaseQuery`    |
| Create / Update / Delete                      | `useBaseMutation` |
| Paginated list / infinite scroll              | `useBaseInfinite` |
| Global auth state / side effects across sagas | Redux + saga      |

## 6. Navigation

### Route Names

Use `AppRoutes` enum — NEVER magic strings:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
navigation.navigate(AppRoutes.Home);

// ❌ BAD
navigation.navigate('Home');
```

### Adding a New Screen

**Always wrap screen with `Wrapper` component** from `~components/common`:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { Header, Safe, Wrapper } from '~components/common';

const NewScreen = () => (
  <Wrapper>
    <Header title="Screen Title" />
    {/* content */}
    <Safe />
  </Wrapper>
);

// ❌ BAD — missing Wrapper
const BadScreen = () => (
  <View>
    <Text>Content</Text>
  </View>
);
```

**Define route in 2 places:**

1. Add route to `AppRoutes` enum in `src/configs/constants/routes.ts`:

```ts
export enum AppRoutes {
  HOME = 'Home',
  NEW_SCREEN = 'NewScreen', // add here
}
```

2. Add param type to `AppStackParamList` in `src/types/navigation.type.ts`:

```ts
export type AppStackParamList = {
  [AppRoutes.HOME]: undefined;
  [AppRoutes.NEW_SCREEN]: undefined; // add here
};
```

### Navigation Inside Components

Use typed wrappers — NEVER the raw hooks:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
const navigation = useAppNavigation<AppStackParamList>();
const route = useAppRoute<AppRoutes.Home>();

// ❌ BAD
const navigation = useNavigation();
```

### Navigation Outside React (sagas, services)

Use `navigationService` singleton:

```tsx
import { navigationService } from '~services/navigation.service';

navigationService.navigate(AppRoutes.Home);
navigationService.reset({ index: 0, routes: [{ name: AppRoutes.Login }] });
```

## 7. API & Services

### Service Objects — plain objects, NOT classes

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
export const postService = {
  getById: (id: string): Promise<Post> => request.get(`/posts/${id}`),
  create: (payload: CreatePostPayload): Promise<Post> => request.post('/posts', payload),
};

// ❌ BAD — class-based service
class PostService { ... }
```

### Use request wrapper — NEVER call axios directly

```tsx
import request from '~utils/request';

const data = await request.get<ResponseType>('/endpoint');
const data = await request.post<ResponseType>('/endpoint', payload);
```

### Environment Variables

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { API_URL } from '~configs/constants';

// ❌ BAD
const url = 'https://api.example.com';
```

### Storage

```tsx
import { StorageService } from '~services/storage.service';
import { StorageEnum } from '~configs/constants';

StorageService.set(StorageEnum.AccessToken, token);
const token = StorageService.getString(StorageEnum.AccessToken);
```

## 8. Forms (react-hook-form + yup)

```tsx
const schema = yup.object({ email: yup.string().email().required() });

const { control, handleSubmit } = useForm<FormValues>({
  resolver: yupResolver(schema),
});

// Use FormInput with control prop — NEVER raw TextInput
<FormInput control={control} name="email" type="text" ... />
```

## 9. Common Components

Always use components from `~components/common` instead of raw React Native equivalents:

### Text

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { Text } from '~components/common';
<Text style={tw`text-sm text-gray-900`}>Hello</Text>;

// ❌ BAD
import { Text } from 'react-native';
```

### Modal

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { Modal } from '~components/common';

// ❌ BAD
import { Modal } from 'react-native';
```

## 10. i18n

Always use `useLanguages` hook — NEVER hardcode user-facing strings:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { useLanguages } from '~hooks';

const { t } = useLanguages();
<Text>{t('common.submit')}</Text>;

// ❌ BAD — use react-i18next directly
import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';
```

The `useLanguages` hook wraps `useTranslation` and handles language persistence automatically.

## 11. Persistence

- Only the `auth` slice is persisted (MMKV via `mmkvStorage` adapter)
- Never add new slices to persist whitelist without considering privacy/performance
- Never import `AsyncStorage` — always use `StorageService` or MMKV directly

## 12. Creating New Components

### Folder Structure

```
src/components/<category>/
├── index.ts           # barrel export
├── ComponentName.tsx  # component + default export
├── ComponentName2.tsx
└── index.ts
```

### Component File Pattern

```tsx
// ✅ MyComponent.tsx
import React from 'react';
import { View } from 'react-native';
import tw from '~configs/tw';

interface MyComponentProps {
  title: string;
  onPress?: () => void;
}

export function MyComponent({ title, onPress }: MyComponentProps) {
  return <View style={tw`p-4`}>{title}</View>;
}

export default MyComponent;
```

### Barrel index.ts Pattern

```ts
// ✅ index.ts
// ─── Components ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
export { default as MyComponent } from './MyComponent';
export { default as AnotherComponent } from './AnotherComponent';

// ─── Props ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
export type { MyComponentProps } from './MyComponent';
export type { AnotherComponentProps } from './AnotherComponent';
```

### Rules

- Use **named function declaration** (`export function`) — NOT arrow function
- Always include **both named AND default export**
- Props defined as **local interface** above the component
- Import `tw` from `~configs/tw` — never create new instance
- Use components from `~components/common` instead of raw React Native

## 13. Creating New Hooks

### When to Create a Hook

Create a custom hook when:

- Logic is reused across multiple components
- Logic needs to manage state or side effects
- Logic is complex and should be isolated

### Folder Structure

```
src/hooks/
├── index.ts           # barrel export
├── useMyHook.ts       # hook file
├── useAnotherHook.ts
└── index.ts
```

### Hook File Pattern

```ts
// ✅ useMyHook.ts
import { useState, useCallback } from 'react';

export function useMyHook(initialValue: string) {
  const [value, setValue] = useState(initialValue);

  const reset = useCallback(() => {
    setValue(initialValue);
  }, [initialValue]);

  return { value, setValue, reset };
}
```

### Common Reusable Hooks

| Hook           | Purpose                                                   |
| -------------- | --------------------------------------------------------- |
| `useDidMount`  | Run callback once on mount (like componentDidMount)       |
| `useDidUpdate` | Run callback when dependencies change (skip first render) |
| `usePrevious`  | Get previous value of a variable                          |
| `useInterval`  | Set up an interval that auto-clears on unmount            |
| `useRefresh`   | Provide a refresh function for React Query                |

### Rules

- Use **named function declaration** (`export function`) — NOT arrow function
- Hook name must start with `use` prefix
- Import from `~hooks` path alias
- Keep hooks focused — one responsibility per hook
- Extract reusable logic into hooks, not components

## 14. TypeScript Strictness

### No `any` Type

Never use `any` — always define proper types:

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
const handleData = (data: any) => { ... };

// ✅ GOOD
interface UserData {
  id: string;
  name: string;
}
const handleData = (data: UserData) => { ... };
```

### Generic Types

Use generics for reusable components and functions:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — generic component
export function List<T>({ items, renderItem }: ListProps<T>) {
  return items.map((item, index) => renderItem(item, index));
}

// ✅ GOOD — generic function
function parseResponse<T>(response: ApiResponse<T>): T {
  return response.data;
}
```

### Type Inference

Let TypeScript infer types when obvious:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — TypeScript infers 'string'
const name = 'John';

// ✅ GOOD — explicit type when not obvious
const fetchUser = async (): Promise<User> => { ... };
```

## 15. Performance Optimization

### useCallback for Callbacks

Wrap callback functions in `useCallback` when passed as props:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — stable callback reference
const onPress = useCallback(() => {
  doSomething(value);
}, [value]);

<Button onPress={onPress} />

// ❌ BAD — new function every render
<Button onPress={() => doSomething(value)} />
```

### useMemo for Expensive Computations

Memoize expensive calculations:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
const sortedList = useMemo(() => {
  return items.slice().sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));
}, [items]);

// ❌ BAD — sorting on every render
const sortedList = items.slice().sort(...);
```

### React.memo for Pure Components

Wrap components that re-render unnecessarily:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
const ExpensiveList = React.memo(({ items }) => {
  return items.map(item => <Item key={item.id} {...item} />);
});

// ❌ BAD — all items re-render when any item changes
const ExpensiveList = ({ items }) => { ... };
```

## 16. Conditional Rendering

### Use ternary for simple conditions

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — simple conditional
{
  isLoading ? <Spinner /> : <Content />;
}

// ❌ BAD — ternary for complex logic
{
  isLoading ? <Spinner /> : data ? <Content /> : <Empty />;
}
```

### Use logical operators for guard clauses

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — render based on condition
{
  showBanner && <Banner />;
}
{
  error && <ErrorMessage error={error} />;
}

// ❌ BAD — complex conditionals in JSX
{
  user && user.isAdmin && user.permissions && <AdminPanel />;
}
```

### Extract complex conditions

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — readable condition
const canShowAdminPanel = user?.isAdmin && hasPermission;
{
  canShowAdminPanel && <AdminPanel />;
}

// ❌ BAD — inline complex logic
{
  user?.isAdmin && user.permissions?.includes('admin') && !isLoading && (
    <AdminPanel />
  );
}
```

## 17. Console Logs

### Remove console statements before production

Never leave `console.log`, `console.warn`, `console.error` in production:

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — console statements left in code
console.log('API response:', data);
console.warn('Deprecated method used');

// ✅ GOOD — use conditional console in development only
if (__DEV__) {
  console.log('API response:', data);
}

// ✅ GOOD — use proper logging service for production
logger.info('API response', { data });
```

## 18. Constants Organization

### Centralize constants in `src/configs/constants/`

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — structured constants
src/configs/constants/
├── routes.ts      // AppRoutes enum
├── storage.ts     // StorageEnum
├── api.ts         // API endpoints, timeouts
└── index.ts       // re-export all

// ✅ GOOD — use typed constants
import { AppRoutes } from '~configs/constants';
navigation.navigate(AppRoutes.HOME);
```

### Avoid magic strings/numbers

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — magic values
const timeout = 5000;
const maxRetries = 3;

// ✅ GOOD — named constants
import { API_TIMEOUT, MAX_RETRIES } from '~configs/constants';
```
